---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="About" description="About HvyRlr — AI Architect & Builder">
  <div class="max-w-2xl">
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-6">About</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg">
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        I'm an experienced technology consultant learning as much as possible about
        Agentic AI by building working agentic systems.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        The governing principle: this work exists to <strong class="text-gray-200">produce things, not just store things</strong>.
        Every project in the pipeline is a real deliverable — working code, live interviews,
        structured knowledge, deployed sites.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">What I'm building</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        The AI Agency Pipeline is a fully (or highly) automated workflow covering the complete
        ideation-to-deployment lifecycle for technology solutions. A client need or idea goes in
        one end; a working, deployed solution comes out the other — with minimal human intervention.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        I'm building it by building with it. Every component is designed and tested on real
        problems — client discovery interviews, knowledge ingestion, automated pipelines,
        and this website.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Design principles</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-indigo-700 pl-4">
          <p class="text-white font-medium mb-1">Agile</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Build only what's needed to accomplish the current goal. Identify extension paths but don't build them until the problem is real.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-indigo-700 pl-4">
          <p class="text-white font-medium mb-1">Maintainability</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Every design decision addresses how the component will be maintained over time. Design for operability, not just functionality.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-indigo-700 pl-4">
          <p class="text-white font-medium mb-1">Single Source of Truth</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">The Learn & Retain KB is the SSOT for the entire pipeline. All projects read from it before starting, write back when done.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Tech stack</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        {[
          ['AI / Intelligence', 'Anthropic API, Claude Code, Claude Sonnet & Haiku'],
          ['Knowledge', 'Obsidian vault, Chroma vector DB (planned)'],
          ['Data Processing', 'Python 3.14, youtube-transcript-api, yt-dlp'],
          ['DevOps', 'GitHub, Vercel, GitHub Actions'],
          ['Web', 'Astro, Tailwind CSS'],
          ['Infrastructure', 'macOS, cron, Python venv'],
        ].map(([layer, tech]) => (
          <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-3">
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">{layer}</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">{tech}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Page>
